noteString: Four - links to Day Notes - (today + 2 days)
extendedNoteString:
The test setup code will need to create the Group and its content.
The date to use should be today's date, plus two 
(even if that puts us into the next month/year).

The count here is the same as the non-calendar types, plus one more case for
when there is no pre-existing group to link to but for Calendar types we can
still make such a link.

targetNoteInfo.noteString: Get 'my' closet content down to 'my' stuff, only
targetNoteInfo.extendedNoteString: We now have extra closet space in the cottage; Nina just needs to clear out.

There are now three movie trilogies in the Star Wars universe.
The original (middle of the timeline) trilogy was so long ago (and so good) that it has already been rewatched by me, many times.  Then there was the prequel trilogy, the animated clone wars, and then the final trilogy, with a couple of one-offs thrown in.  Now a final Clone Wars season 7 is released (and not yet seen by me), and it comes so far after watching the first 6 that they should be rewatched as a lead-up to the new season.  But now, the official timeline indicates that this series takes place within the prequel trilogy, so to get the proper bearings, that one should also be rewatched, with everything seen in the correct order (as detailed in the new text file in my video notes on that subject).  So the decision is to rewatch the prequel trilogy and clone wars movie and series, all in the correct timeline order, and then stop there without revisiting the original (mid-timeline) trilogy simce I'm not ready to go there yet again.  And the final trilogy in the timeline and the one-offs have been seen too recently to do them again at this time.
